{
  "stem": "10588.7",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When mass murder of the Jews becomes legal under the banner of an ideology or God's sacred name, then it is not the victims, but the Nazi murderers who did not resist Satan and have defiled God's name.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When living skeletons are marching at gunpoint through the gates of Auschwitz in long columns of five, cold, starved, forced to hard labor, what power on Earth gave them the strength to survive?",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When all heads are shaved, all human rights denied, and all wear the same kind of tattered striped dress, when to worship-- the worship of God becomes a crime, then the whole world is in a terrible mess.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When Hitler's dream becomes a reality and the Nazis send Jews to the left and to the right, then such men are not ruled by God's divine power, but by their own burning ambition for power and might.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When this so-called superior Aryan master race used all their technology, knowledge, and skill to murder six million Jews merely for being born Jewish, that was not God's, but Hitler's demonic will.'",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Hope never.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Hope never.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Even in the time when I was praying for-- for death, I didn't lose hope.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's just that I-- I couldn't-- I didn't know how to deal with the pain.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't think I really wanted to die.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I just probably prayed for a relief of the pain.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I didn't know how to express it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because the very fact that-- once I found out that they want us dead, I did everything to survive.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I tried to keep myself as clean as I could, because I know that made a big difference, as healthy as I could, mental attitude, and above all, not to give up hope, because my parents and my grandmother used to say, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 43
    }
  ],
